tracker: tracker (semantic data storage search engine)
tracker:
tracker: Tracker is a search engine and that allows the user to find their
tracker: data as fast as possible. Users can search for their files and search
tracker: for content in their files too.  Tracker is a semantic data storage
tracker: for desktop and mobile devices.  Tracker uses W3C standards for RDF
tracker: ontologies using Nepomuk with SPARQL to query and update the data.
tracker: Tracker is a central repository of user information, that provides
tracker: two big benefits for the desktop; shared data between applications
tracker: and information which is relational to other information (e.g. mixing
tracker: contacts with files, locations, activities and etcetera).
